fields.name: errorCode
fields.description: SQL error code

fields.name: sqlState
fields.description: SQL state

fields.name: executionResults
fields.description: Result of execution of commands

records.name: BatchExecuteErrorDetail
records.description: Represents the properties belonging to a `BatchExecuteError`.

fields.name: maxOpenConnections
fields.description:
The maximum number of open connections that the pool is allowed to have, including
both idle and in-use connections. Default value is 15 and it can be changed through the
configuration API with the key `b7a.sql.pool.maxOpenConnections`.

fields.name: maxConnectionLifeTime
fields.description:
The maximum lifetime (in seconds) of a connection in the pool. Default value is 1800
seconds (30 minutes) and it can be changed through the configuration API with the
key `b7a.sql.pool.maxConnectionLifeTime`. A value of 0 indicates unlimited maximum
lifetime (infinite lifetime).

fields.name: minIdleConnections
fields.description:
The minimum number of idle connections that pool tries to maintain in the pool. Default
is the same as maxOpenConnections and it can be changed through the configuration
API with the key `b7a.sql.pool.minIdleConnections`.

records.name: ConnectionPool
records.description:
Represents the properties which are used to configure DB connection pool.
Default values of the fields can be set through the configuration API.

fields.name: errorCode
fields.description: SQL error code

fields.name: sqlState
fields.description: SQL state

records.name: DatabaseErrorDetail
records.description: Represents the properties belonging to a `DatabaseError`.

fields.name: affectedRowCount
fields.description:
Number of rows affected by the execution of the query. It may be one of the following,
(1) A number greater than or equal to zero -- indicates that the command was processed
successfully and is the affected row count in the database that were affected by
the command's execution
(2) A value of `SUCCESS_NO_INFO` indicates that the command was processed successfully but
that the number of rows affected is unknown
(3) A value of `EXECUTION_FAILED` indicated the specific command failed. This can be returned
in `BatchExecuteError` and only if the driver continues to process the statements after
the error occurred.

fields.name: lastInsertId
fields.description:
The integer or string generated by the database in response to a query execution.
Typically this will be from an "auto increment" column when inserting a new row. Not all databases
support this feature, and hence it can be also nil.

records.name: ExecutionResult
records.description: The result of the query without returning the rows.

parameters.name: sqlQuery
parameters.description:
The query which needs to be executed as `string` or `ParameterizedQuery` when the SQL query has
params to be passed in

parameters.name: rowType
parameters.description:
The `typedesc` of the record that should be returned as a result. If this is not provided the default
column names of the query result set be used for the record attributes

returnParameters.description: Stream of records in the type of `rowType`

methods.name: query
methods.description: Queries the database with the query provided by the user, and returns the result as stream.

parameters.name: sqlQuery
parameters.description:
The DDL or DML query such as INSERT, DELETE, UPDATE, etc as `string` or `ParameterizedQuery`
when the query has params to be passed in

returnParameters.description:
Summary of the sql update query as `ExecutionResult` or an `Error`
if any error occurred when executing the query

methods.name: execute
methods.description: Executes the DDL or DML sql query provided by the user, and returns summary of the execution.

parameters.name: sqlQueries
parameters.description:
The DDL or DML query such as INSERT, DELETE, UPDATE, etc as `ParameterizedQuery` with an array
of values passed in

returnParameters.description:
Summary of the executed SQL queries as `ExecutionResult[]` which includes details such as
`affectedRowCount` and `lastInsertId`. If one of the commands in the batch fails, this function
will return `BatchExecuteError`, however the driver may or may not continue to process the
remaining commands in the batch after a failure. The summary of the executed queries in case of error
can be accessed as `(<sql:BatchExecuteError> result).detail()?.executionResults`.

methods.name: batchExecute
methods.description:
Executes a batch of parameterized DDL or DML sql query provided by the user,
and returns the summary of the execution.

parameters.name: sqlQuery
parameters.description: The query to execute the SQL stored procedure

parameters.name: rowTypes
parameters.description:
The array of `typedesc` of the records that should be returned as a result. If this is not provided
the default column names of the query result set be used for the record attributes.

returnParameters.description: Summary of the execution is returned in `ProcedureCallResult` or `sql:Error`

methods.name: call
methods.description: Executes a SQL stored procedure and returns the result as stream and execution summary.

returnParameters.description: Possible error during closing the client

methods.name: close
methods.description: Close the SQL client.
